Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs)
Q1: Why is NVH more important for EVs than ICE vehicles?
A: With no engine noise, other sounds (road, wind, motor whine) become more noticeable, requiring better NVH control.
Q2: What's the lightest NVH material available today?
A: Advanced polyurethane foams and aerogel composites offer the best weight-to-performance ratio.
Q3: Which automaker uses the most NVH materials?
A: Luxury brands (Mercedes, BMW, Lexus) use 2-3x more NVH materials than economy vehicles.
Q4: Are there sustainable alternatives to traditional NVH materials?
A: Yes, natural fiber composites and recycled rubber are gaining traction.
Q5: How much does NVH treatment add to a vehicle's weight?
A: Typically 15-30kg in premium vehicles, but new materials are reducing this.
